==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''bigeminus'', "doubled". ''bi-'' + ''geminus'', "two" + "double".

===Adjective===
'''bigeminal'''

# occuring in [[pair|pairs]]; doubled or twinned
#:For example, ''a bigeminal pulse''

===Noun===
'''bigeminal'''

# the occurrence of [[premature]] [[atrial]] or [[ventricular]] heartbeats in pairs

